{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb9988b8b-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3284"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3284"},"text":"§ 3284.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Concealment of bankrupt’s assets","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The concealment of assets of a debtor in a case under title 11 shall be deemed to be a continuing offense until the debtor shall have been finally discharged or a discharge denied, and the period of limitations shall not begin to run until such final discharge or denial of discharge.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb9988b8c-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 645","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/828"},"text":"62 Stat. 828","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598/tIII/s314/k"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598, title III, § 314(k)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-06"},"text":"Nov. 6, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2678"},"text":"92 Stat. 2678","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb9988b8d-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb9988b8e-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s52/d"},"text":"section 52(d) of title 11","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., 1940 ed., Bankruptcy ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1926-05-27/ch406/s11d"},"text":"May 27, 1926, ch. 406, § 11d","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/44/665"},"text":"44 Stat. 665","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1938-06-22/ch575/s1"},"text":"June 22, 1938, ch. 575, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/856"},"text":"52 Stat. 856","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The 3-year-limitation provision was omitted as unnecessary in view of the general statute, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s3282"},"text":"section 3282 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The words “or a discharge denied” and “or denial of discharge” were added on the recommendation of the Department of Justice to supply an omission in existing law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Other subsections of said ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s52"},"text":"section 52 of title 11","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., 1940 ed., are incorporated in sections 151–154 and 3057 of this title."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Other minor changes of phraseology were made.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb9988b8f-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb9988b90-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1978—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":" substituted “debtor in a case under title 11” for “bankrupt or other debtor”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb9988b91-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb9988b92-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1978 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1979","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598/s402/a"},"text":"section 402(a) of Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s101"},"text":"section 101 of Title 11","children":[],"tail":", Bankruptcy."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"savings","id":"idb9988b93-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Savings Provision","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598/s314"},"text":"section 314 of Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":" not to affect the application of chapter 9 (§ 151 et seq.), chapter 96 (§ 1961 et seq.), or section 2516, 3057, or 3284 of this title to any act of any person (1) committed before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1979","children":[],"tail":", or (2) committed after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1979","children":[],"tail":", in connection with a case commenced before such date, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598/s403/d"},"te